=head1 DESCRIPTION

How the auto-merging process should resolve conflicts between different
profiles.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ConflictResolvingModel => Str

How the auto-merging process should resolve conflicts between different
profiles.

=over

=item *

C<RECENCY>: Uses the data that was most recently updated.

=item *

C<SOURCE>: Uses the data from a specific source. For example, if a
company has been aquired or two departments have merged, data from the
specified source is used. If two duplicate profiles are from the same
source, then C<RECENCY> is used again.

=back



=head2 SourceName => Str

The C<ObjectType> name that is used to resolve profile merging
conflicts when choosing C<SOURCE> as the C<ConflictResolvingModel>.



